# UI Mockup Generation Skill (Core Banking Software — HTML + Tailwind)

Turns a `05-ui-ux/**/*-screen.md` spec into a **layout-only** HTML prototype for bank-user review. Mockups are shareable without Angular, Cursor, or a dev environment. After approval, `@generate-ui-screen` converts the approved HTML structure into production Angular code with full i18n (`mr` + `en`).

## Standing Decisions

| Decision | Value |
|---|---|
| Styling | **Tailwind CSS v4** via CDN: `<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tailwindcss/browser@4"></script>` |
| Shared theme | [`mockup-base.css`](../../documentation/05-ui-ux/mockups/shared/mockup-base.css) — plain CSS linked via `<link rel="stylesheet">` (component classes, form controls, tokens) |
| Tailwind in HTML | Layout utilities only (`max-w-4xl`, `grid`, `flex`, `bg-gray-100`, etc.) via CDN class scanning |
| Mockup language | **Marathi only** — no English labels, no language toggle in mockups |
| Angular i18n | English added during `@generate-ui-screen` via `ngx-translate` (spec has both labels) |
| Interactivity | **Layout-only** — tab switching only; no form validation or API calls |
| Deliverable format | Static `index.html` + `README.md` in repo (no separate `styles.css` unless screen-specific overrides needed) |
| Master data gaps (`TODO`) | Show placeholder with `[TODO]` badge — never invent values |
| Layout | **Centered container** `max-w-7xl mx-auto` on gray page background |
| Section layout | On `≥1024px`, pair related sections side-by-side via `.mockup-section-columns` (e.g. Basic Info left, Settings right); full-width sections for grids/tables |

## Core Principles

- **Spec is the source of truth.** Every field, tab, section, grid column, and action must trace to a row in the screen's `.md` file.
- **Simplicity first.** Layout optimized for cooperative bank staff (Clerk/Cashier) — clear grouping, visible required markers, generous spacing, no clutter.
- **UI simplification patterns.** Before authoring or updating specs/mockups, read [ui-simplification-patterns.md](../../documentation/05-ui-ux/shared/ui-simplification-patterns.md). Use **प्रगत सेटिंग्ज (Advanced Settings)** for technical fields; render auto-generated values as read-only; hide conditional fields until their parent is set (do not show disabled controls).
- **Current specs only.** Mockups target **non-superseded** screen specs. If a spec has a Superseded banner, use the linked replacement spec. Check `<domain>/ux-optimization.md` when present.
- **Traceability.** Every form control gets `data-spec-field="<row#>"` matching the spec table's `#` column.
- **No invented master data.** Dropdown options marked `TODO` render as disabled options with a visible badge.
- **Marathi labels only in mockups.** Use the Marathi column from the spec. English labels are deferred to Angular i18n generation.

## Execution Workflow (always follow in order)

1. **Read [`AI_INDEX.md`](../../documentation/AI_INDEX.md)**, then the target `*-screen.md`, its module `overview.md`, `changelog.md`, and [ui-simplification-patterns.md](../../documentation/05-ui-ux/shared/ui-simplification-patterns.md) if the domain has been optimized.
2. **Skip superseded specs.** If the spec starts with `Superseded`, locate the replacement from `overview.md` or `ux-optimization.md` and mockup that file instead.
3. **Resolve output path** from spec location:
   - Spec: `documentation/05-ui-ux/<module>/.../<screen-name>.md`
   - Mockup: `documentation/05-ui-ux/mockups/<module>/.../<screen-name>/`
3. **Check reference screenshots** listed in the spec. If missing from repo, note in `README.md` — proceed spec-driven.
4. **Read sibling specs** when a tab defers to another screen.
5. **Generate mockup files** (see Output Structure below).
6. **Link mockup from spec** — ensure `## Mockup` section exists on the screen spec.
7. **Update module `changelog.md`** with mockup entry.
8. **Run Pre-Completion Checklist** before reporting done.

## Output Structure

```text
documentation/05-ui-ux/mockups/<module>/<screen-name>/
  index.html      # Tailwind HTML, Marathi labels, data-spec-field attributes
  README.md       # open instructions, review checklist, approval status
```

Optional `styles.css` only when screen-specific Tailwind overrides cannot live in `index.html`.

### index.html template (head)

```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Noto+Sans+Devanagari:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tailwindcss/browser@4"></script>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../../../shared/mockup-base.css">
```

**Tailwind browser build limitations (file:// mockups):**
- Do **not** use `@import` inside `<style type="text/tailwindcss">`
- Do **not** use `@apply` in custom CSS — use plain CSS in `mockup-base.css` instead
- Tailwind CDN is for **HTML utility classes only**; shared components use `.mockup-*` classes from `mockup-base.css`

### index.html requirements

- `<html lang="mr">` — Marathi only, no language toggle
- Content in `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
- Header: screen title + breadcrumb (Marathi) from spec **Screen Identification** table
- **Module screen nav** (when the module has 2+ mockup screens): immediately after `</header>`, add a `.mockup-module-nav` bar linking sibling screens in the same `mockups/<module>/` folder only — no cross-module links. Current screen = `<span class="mockup-module-nav-link mockup-module-nav-current" aria-current="page">`; siblings = `<a href="…" class="mockup-module-nav-link">`. Use relative paths (`../<screen>/index.html`; for nested modules like `settings/*`, use `../../<subfolder>/<screen>/index.html`). Styles live in `mockup-base.css`.
- Tab bar from spec **Tabs** table — use `.mockup-tab` / `.mockup-tab-active`
- Sections from spec `### Section:` headings — use `.mockup-section` / `.mockup-section-title`
- **Side-by-side sections** on desktop: wrap paired sections in `.mockup-section-columns` (2 equal columns at `≥1024px`); keep grids/tables in `.mockup-section-full`
- Fields inside side-by-side sections: `.mockup-field-grid` (1 col) or `.mockup-field-grid--2` (2 cols within each half)
- Required fields: `<span class="mockup-required">*</span>` when spec `Required: Yes`
- Grids: `.mockup-table` with horizontal scroll wrapper on mobile
- Sticky footer: `fixed bottom-0` action bar aligned to same `max-w-4xl` container
- Footer buttons (Marathi): रीसेट, मागे (tab 2+), पुढे (tab 1), जतन करा (last tab)
- Minimal JS: tab switching only

### Field type mapping

| Spec Type | HTML element |
|---|---|
| Textbox | `<input type="text">` or `<input type="password">` when masked |
| Dropdown | `<select>` — known default as selected option; `TODO` values as disabled `<option>` |
| Radio | `<input type="radio">` group with `<fieldset>` |
| Checkbox | `<input type="checkbox">` |
| Date | `<input type="date">` |
| Label (read-only) | `<span>` with muted styling |
| Autocomplete | `<input type="text" class="mockup-autocomplete" list="…">` + matching `<datalist>` with sample `id — name` options from [entity-autocomplete-pattern.md](../../documentation/05-ui-ux/shared/entity-autocomplete-pattern.md); one control per Branch/GL/Account lookup |
| Disabled until checkbox | `disabled` attribute + grayed label |

