## How to open

Open `index.html` in any web browser. Requires internet for Tailwind CDN and Google Fonts.

## Review checklist

- [ ] All spec fields present with correct grouping
- [ ] Marathi labels clear for non-technical bank staff
- [ ] Required fields marked with *
- [ ] Responsive on mobile (single column) and desktop (two columns, centered)
- [ ] Grid columns match spec
- [ ] Tab structure approved

## Approval

When approved, change Status to **Approved**. Then run `/generate-ui-screen <screen-name>`.
```

## UX Standards

| Breakpoint | Layout |
|---|---|
| `< 640px` (mobile) | Single-column form; tabs scroll horizontally; tables scroll horizontally |
| `≥ 1024px` (desktop) | `.mockup-section-columns` — related sections side-by-side; `max-w-7xl` container uses horizontal space |
| Wide desktop | Modest gray margins outside container; org-rights / data grids stay full width |

Non-negotiable:
- Noto Sans Devanagari font for Marathi readability
- Every control has an associated `<label>`
- Visible keyboard focus styles
- Sticky action bar so Save/Next never scrolls out of view
- `TODO` items visibly marked, never filled with guessed data

## Pre-Completion Checklist

- [ ] Module screen nav (`.mockup-module-nav`) links all sibling screens in the same module when 2+ exist
- [ ] Advanced Settings section collapsed by default when spec defines `प्रगत सेटिंग्ज`
- [ ] Branch/GL/Account lookup fields use single Autocomplete control (not legacy ID + select pairs)
- [ ] Every spec field/column has HTML with `data-spec-field`
- [ ] Marathi labels only — no duplicate EN spans or language toggle
- [ ] Tailwind CDN loaded; `mockup-base.css` linked as regular stylesheet (plain CSS, no `@apply`)
- [ ] Show/hide uses `.mockup-hidden` (not Tailwind `hidden`) for tab/button toggling
- [ ] Centered `max-w-7xl` layout; side-by-side sections on desktop where form is long
- [ ] Responsive grid and sticky action bar
- [ ] `README.md` has review checklist and Status: Draft

